0:The weak light of the setting sun was pouring through the window of the hospital room.[%p]
100:The color of sunset split the room cleanly between light and shadow.[%p]
200:Inside the light was...[%p]
300:A bed with pure white sheets. A portable gaming system sitting by the pillow.[%p]
400:Rows of academic books sitting on a shelf. Light pink cosmos flowers sitting in a vase.[%p]
500:The room was neat and organized. Nothing moved. It was a room where time had stopped.[%p]
600:Near the window, where the sunlight shone through... There was someone small, sitting in a wheelchair.[%p]
700:His back was to the window, and he wasn't moving. His breathing was so gentle and deep that you'd wonder if he might be dead.[%p]
800:His skin was wrinkled, his cheeks caved in.[%p]
900:His eyes sank deep into his skull. He had no hair at all on his head.[%p]
1000:Looking at him, it was unclear if he was a boy or an old man.[%p]
1100:The shadow of the one who called himself “Shogun” stretched all the way to the room's door.[%p]
1200:For the first time, the world moved. The door slowly opened, and someone came from the dark hallway into the evening light.[%p]
1300:Rimi Sakihata stood at the entrance to the room. She didn't come in any further.[%p]
1400:The setting sun illuminated her face, revealing the tension in her expression.[%p]
